###
### Delete user configuration (resets to defaults)
# @name delete-user-config
DELETE {{host}}/api/user-config/user-id-0
x-ms-correlation-id: {{$guid}}

###
# Usage Instructions:
# 1. Start Hermes locally: dotnet run --project Hermes
# 2. Replace "user-id-0" with your actual Teams User ID (format: 29:...)
#    - Get it by sending a message to the bot in Teams
#    - Check Cosmos DB emulator: https://localhost:8081/_explorer/index.html
#    - Look in ConversationReference container for your TeamsUserId
# 3. Execute requests in order:
#    a) GET to check current config (or confirm it doesn't exist)
#    b) PUT to set custom preferences
#    c) GET again to verify the update
#    d) DELETE to reset to defaults
#
# Default settings (if no configuration exists):
# - SLA violation notifications: Enabled
# - Work item update notifications: Disabled
# - Max per hour: 5
# - Max per day: 20
# - Quiet hours: Disabled
# - Timezone: UTC
#
# Timezone Notes:
# - Use IANA timezone identifiers (e.g., "America/Los_Angeles", "Asia/Kolkata", "Europe/London")
# - Quiet hours times are interpreted in the user's local timezone
# - Example: If timeZoneId is "America/Los_Angeles" and quietHours are 22:00-08:00,
#   those times are 10 PM - 8 AM Pacific Time (automatically handles PST/PDT)
# - Invalid timezone IDs fallback to UTC
# - Common timezones:
#   - US Pacific: "America/Los_Angeles"
#   - US Eastern: "America/New_York"
#   - India: "Asia/Kolkata"
#   - UK: "Europe/London"
#   - Japan: "Asia/Tokyo"
#   - Australia (Sydney): "Australia/Sydney"
